cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on scalability of a state-of-the-art Deep Reinforcement Learning algorithm, which is a subfield of Machine Learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with optimization algorithms and memory footprint, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of synchronous training and minimizing memory footprint also relates to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of neural networks and optimization algorithms falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
